WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.250
♪ Ahh, push it ♪

00:04.250 --> 00:05.500
Curtis: We're running
out of hotels.

00:05.500 --> 00:06.880
Have you seen my purse?

00:06.880 --> 00:09.040
Five-star hotels.
I could've sworn --

00:09.040 --> 00:10.960
We're not gonna take this show
to the Super 8 next, are we?

00:10.960 --> 00:12.500
'Cause something tells me

00:12.500 --> 00:13.920
you like the five-star service
you've been getting.

00:13.920 --> 00:16.330
Oh, you're giving yourself
five stars now?

00:16.330 --> 00:17.670
[ Chuckles ]
You can tell me I'm wrong.

00:17.670 --> 00:21.830
♪♪

00:21.830 --> 00:22.710
I'll be in touch.

00:22.710 --> 00:24.290
Your assistant --
What?

00:24.290 --> 00:25.620
Your assistant
will be touch.

00:25.620 --> 00:27.170
My assistant handles
my schedule.

00:27.170 --> 00:29.580
So, then, dinner,
a night out?

00:29.580 --> 00:31.500
Maybe your assistant
can schedule me in?

00:31.500 --> 00:33.120
I'm just saying,
this five-star service

00:33.120 --> 00:35.540
could extend
to outside the hotel room, too.

00:35.540 --> 00:36.790
Curtis...

00:36.790 --> 00:37.830
my assistant handles

00:37.830 --> 00:40.670
my very busy schedule.

00:40.670 --> 00:42.540
If I'm having a day,

00:42.540 --> 00:44.460
if my tea isn't sitting
on my desk,

00:44.460 --> 00:45.790
piping hot in the morning,

00:45.790 --> 00:47.880
if the President ignores

00:47.880 --> 00:49.210
something I've said
in the afternoon,

00:49.210 --> 00:51.040
if the state dinner
I'm throwing

00:51.040 --> 00:52.920
for the head of state
who's in town

00:52.920 --> 00:54.380
is a bust in the evening --

00:54.380 --> 00:57.670
that is where you and your
five-star service come in.

00:57.670 --> 00:59.880
♪♪

00:59.880 --> 01:02.790
I'm really not sure how
to make myself any more clear.

01:02.790 --> 01:05.250
So, is that your way of saying
you don't need a date

01:05.250 --> 01:06.500
for the state dinner
tomorrow night?

01:06.500 --> 01:07.830
[ Groans ]
'Cause I-I was
kind of hoping that --

01:07.830 --> 01:09.500
Goodbye, Curtis.

01:09.500 --> 01:11.210
♪ Get up on this! ♪
♪ B-Baby, baby ♪

01:17.250 --> 01:18.670
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

01:18.670 --> 01:20.170
Of course,
the state dinner tradition

01:20.170 --> 01:22.380
dates all the way back to 1874,

01:22.380 --> 01:24.170
when President Ulysses S. Grant

01:24.170 --> 01:26.000
welcomed
King Kalakaua of Hawaii,

01:26.000 --> 01:28.620
which, as we all know,
later became our 50th state.

01:28.620 --> 01:31.250
Now, at that dinner,
there were just 36 guests

01:31.250 --> 01:34.170
eating 29 courses,
if you can believe it.

01:34.170 --> 01:37.170
Tonight, President Grant will be
playing host to 120 guests

01:37.170 --> 01:39.000
eating just five courses
at our state dinner

01:39.000 --> 01:40.120
for the President of Bashran.

01:40.120 --> 01:42.460
Excuse me,
what's this tarp?

01:42.460 --> 01:44.830
Oh, that's the old pool built
by President Franklin Roosevelt.

01:44.830 --> 01:46.710
It's under construction.

01:46.710 --> 01:48.710
As some of you may know,
President Roosevelt had polio,

01:48.710 --> 01:50.330
so he actually used the pool t--
[ Footsteps approaching ]

01:50.330 --> 01:52.420
Oh, it's Olivia Pope,
everyone --

01:52.420 --> 01:54.330
our very own Chief of Staff.
Hello, hello.

01:54.330 --> 01:55.790
You all picked a very busy day
to visit the White House.

01:55.790 --> 01:57.420
Welcome.

01:57.420 --> 01:58.380
[ Indistinct murmuring,
camera shutters clicking ]

01:58.380 --> 02:00.420
Mr. Vice President.

02:00.420 --> 02:02.120
[ Door closes ]
I wish you'd stop doing that.

02:02.120 --> 02:04.380
Doing what?
Being so formal.

02:04.380 --> 02:06.210
I'd like this to be informal --

02:06.210 --> 02:07.670
colleagues, but friends.

02:07.670 --> 02:09.000
I see.
You're here to complain?

02:09.000 --> 02:10.830
We were friends once,
weren't we?

02:10.830 --> 02:13.000
But now what am I to you?
At this moment,

02:13.000 --> 02:14.380
we are preparing to host

02:14.380 --> 02:15.620
the president of a country

02:15.620 --> 02:17.500
who just caught us
spying on him --

02:17.500 --> 02:20.170
not a great place to start when
the point of tonight's dinner

02:20.170 --> 02:22.750
is to talk this man into giving
up his nuclear capabilities.

02:22.750 --> 02:23.920
Add on top of that,
the fact that Mellie

02:23.920 --> 02:25.580
doesn't have a a First Lady.

02:25.580 --> 02:27.580
So the questions
I've been forced to field...
[ Sighs ]

02:27.580 --> 02:29.210
...have been about
china patterns,

02:29.210 --> 02:31.620
about centerpieces,
and I am not a wedding planner.

02:31.620 --> 02:33.920
So, what are you to me --
another person in my office

02:33.920 --> 02:35.790
about to bother me
about tonight's dinner.

02:35.790 --> 02:37.710
Unless --
and I would love this --

02:37.710 --> 02:41.120
you can tell me you're here
about something else.

02:41.120 --> 02:43.500
[ Exhales sharply ]
[ Chuckles ]

02:43.500 --> 02:44.670
Out with it.

02:44.670 --> 02:46.290
It's about
tonight's seating arrangement.

02:46.290 --> 02:48.750
Goodbye, Cyrus.
I'm sitting
next to Fenton Glackland --

02:48.750 --> 02:51.420
Fenton Glackland --

02:51.420 --> 02:53.120
which I assume is
no accident.

02:53.120 --> 02:54.120
You assume correctly.

02:54.120 --> 02:56.540
Why, Olivia?
What sin did I commit?

02:56.540 --> 02:58.880
What gods have I offended
that I've been sentenced

02:58.880 --> 03:00.080
to sit for two hours

03:00.080 --> 03:02.120
next to Fenton Glackland?

03:02.120 --> 03:03.880
Or is it because I'm gay,
and he's gay,

03:03.880 --> 03:05.080
and you think we speak

03:05.080 --> 03:06.750
some secret gay language?

03:06.750 --> 03:08.290
You're next to Fenton

03:08.290 --> 03:09.880
because he's one of the biggest
campaign contributors we've got,

03:09.880 --> 03:12.330
and he made a special request
to be seated near you.

03:12.330 --> 03:13.880
Olivia,
we're talking about a man

03:13.880 --> 03:15.460
who wore flip-flops
to his TED Talk.

03:15.460 --> 03:17.080
Look, we've all got our work
cut out for us tonight.

03:17.080 --> 03:19.830
Did I mention Mellie's trying
to charm a dictator

03:19.830 --> 03:21.420
into a nuclear-arms treaty?

03:21.420 --> 03:23.710
The least you can do
is chit-chat

03:23.710 --> 03:26.250
with a billionaire tech mogul
whose support we depend on.

03:26.250 --> 03:27.540
He's a Sasquatch --

03:27.540 --> 03:28.670
a libertarian.

03:28.670 --> 03:29.540
Exactly.

03:29.540 --> 03:31.250
Last election cycle,

03:31.250 --> 03:32.670
he donated on both sides
of the aisle.

03:32.670 --> 03:34.120
Down the line,

03:34.120 --> 03:35.620
when you're mounting
your own campaign,

03:35.620 --> 03:36.960
Glackland could be

03:36.960 --> 03:38.620
a useful person to know.
[ Exhales sharply ]

03:38.620 --> 03:40.330
You want me to be
your friend, Cyrus?

03:40.330 --> 03:42.920
This is me being
your friend.

03:42.920 --> 03:43.920
Get out of my office.

03:43.920 --> 03:45.080
[ Groans ]

03:45.080 --> 03:46.460
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:46.460 --> 03:48.380
You want four tickets
to the state dinner

03:48.380 --> 03:49.330
that's happening tonight.

03:49.330 --> 03:50.120
That's the one.

03:50.120 --> 03:51.710
Yeah, I can't help you.

03:51.710 --> 03:53.290
On the phone, you said
it wouldn't be a problem.

03:53.290 --> 03:54.750
Because I thought
you were asking to be my date,

03:54.750 --> 03:55.880
which would be fine,

03:55.880 --> 03:57.620
but I only get a plus-one,
not a plus-four.

03:57.620 --> 04:00.460
David, we need clients --
high-profile clients --

04:00.460 --> 04:02.830
the kind of clients
that attend state dinners.

04:02.830 --> 04:05.420
Those people came to OPA because
they knew Olivia Pope.

04:05.420 --> 04:07.380
If we want them
to come to QPA,

04:07.380 --> 04:08.330
then they need to know
who we are.

04:08.330 --> 04:09.750
If you all need
to be there that badly,

04:09.750 --> 04:11.330
why don't you
just ask Olivia?

04:11.330 --> 04:13.710
Olivia has a lot on her plate
right now.
And I don't?

04:13.710 --> 04:16.000
Abby, I'm the Attorney General
of the --
Of the United States of America.

04:16.000 --> 04:18.290
Yes, I know,
and you are also my friend,

04:18.290 --> 04:20.210
and I bought you lunch,
so you owe me.

04:20.210 --> 04:21.580
We have lunch together
all the time,

04:21.580 --> 04:23.830
which I always buy,
so technically, you owe me.

04:23.830 --> 04:25.960
You know what?
Let's not get into who owes who.

04:25.960 --> 04:27.170
Abby, I don't know
if you recall,

04:27.170 --> 04:28.960
but you used to work
at the White House.

04:28.960 --> 04:31.420
Yeah, that's the key phrase,
"used to."

04:31.420 --> 04:33.380
You don't think that the idea of
me showing up at the White House

04:33.380 --> 04:36.290
and begging the Social Secretary
for scraps is a little sad?

04:36.290 --> 04:38.040
Is it more sad than the idea
that I can be bought

04:38.040 --> 04:39.880
with a plate of lo-mein
and an egg roll?

04:39.880 --> 04:42.460
They are very good
egg rolls.

04:45.080 --> 04:45.960
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

04:45.960 --> 04:47.380
Abby: We're in!

04:47.380 --> 04:48.790
Four invites
to the state dinner,

04:48.790 --> 04:50.040
all courtesy of David Rosen.

04:50.040 --> 04:52.170
Who's Kevin Dunwoody?
Kevin Dunwoody is you.

04:52.170 --> 04:53.960
We had to give you both
fake identities.

04:53.960 --> 04:55.420
You're not Rihanna
or Adele.

04:55.420 --> 04:56.580
The White House isn't
gonna issue invites

04:56.580 --> 04:57.670
to "Huck" or "Charlie."

04:57.670 --> 04:58.920
I don't know
if I see myself as a Kevin.

04:58.920 --> 05:00.380
You want to be Kevin?
I don't want to go at all.

05:00.380 --> 05:02.040
This is a huge
opportunity,

05:02.040 --> 05:03.380
and we cannot afford
to pass it up.

05:03.380 --> 05:05.080
Plus, I'm the boss,
and I say we're going,

05:05.080 --> 05:06.710
so we're going.
Fake identities?

05:06.710 --> 05:08.500
Infiltrating secure
government buildings?

05:08.500 --> 05:10.710
It does sound a bit like
the good ole days.

05:10.710 --> 05:13.540
♪ Get up on this! ♪

05:13.540 --> 05:15.750
♪ Salt, Salt, Salt,
Salt-N-Pepa's here ♪

05:15.750 --> 05:17.540
Start right in on
the nuclear treaty.

05:17.540 --> 05:19.380
Should I go with
"Mr. President" or --
President Rashad.

05:19.380 --> 05:21.040
He's going to try
to steer you toward

05:21.040 --> 05:22.750
the Joshua Stewart debacle,

05:22.750 --> 05:24.710
seek some sort of apology
for spying on his country but --

05:24.710 --> 05:26.500
[ Sighs ] What's one incident
when a nuclear treaty

05:26.500 --> 05:27.960
equals peace
in the Middle East?

05:27.960 --> 05:29.290
We've only got this brief
meeting and the state dinner

05:29.290 --> 05:30.710
to convince him
to take a bold step.

05:30.710 --> 05:32.830
Got it.

05:32.830 --> 05:33.830
♪ Working up a sweat ♪

05:33.830 --> 05:35.210
President Rashad,
welcome.

05:35.210 --> 05:36.420
Madam President,
thank you.

05:36.420 --> 05:37.540
Being invited here,

05:37.540 --> 05:39.620
as well as having your
undivided attention,

05:39.620 --> 05:40.960
is a great moment
for my country.

05:40.960 --> 05:42.880
As it is for ours.

05:42.880 --> 05:44.710
♪ Push it good ♪

05:44.710 --> 05:46.620
♪ Ahh, push it ♪

05:46.620 --> 05:48.750
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
♪ Push it real good ♪

05:48.750 --> 05:49.710
Thank you, everyone.

05:49.710 --> 05:51.040
Thank you.

05:51.040 --> 05:53.380
I do appreciate you
making the trip.

05:53.380 --> 05:54.710
I hope we can make this
an historic one,

05:54.710 --> 05:56.420
and start down
a very important road

05:56.420 --> 05:57.920
towards
a nuclear-free Bashran.

05:57.920 --> 05:59.080
It is an important road.

05:59.080 --> 06:00.460
And a difficult one, no?

06:00.460 --> 06:02.250
Considering that
your country started this

06:02.250 --> 06:04.380
nuclear-arms race
decades ago

06:04.380 --> 06:06.170
and then escalated it
by handing out

06:06.170 --> 06:08.380
nuclear capabilities
to our enemies,

06:08.380 --> 06:10.750
forcing Bashran to spend
precious resources

06:10.750 --> 06:12.250
just to protect ourselves
on the playground.

06:12.250 --> 06:14.210
Yes, well --
And as you also know,

06:14.210 --> 06:16.210
it is different for a leader,
like myself, to feel secure

06:16.210 --> 06:18.040
when your CIA
provides ammunition

06:18.040 --> 06:20.420
to rebel factions who
want to remove me from power.

06:20.420 --> 06:22.210
But before you tell me

06:22.210 --> 06:24.420
that you're simply trying
to spread democracy,

06:24.420 --> 06:27.210
when, really, you're spreading
lax moral values

06:27.210 --> 06:29.120
and a godless obsession
with sex,

06:29.120 --> 06:32.460
let me just note
that I would be delighted

06:32.460 --> 06:35.540
to discuss the ways to remove
all nuclear weapons

06:35.540 --> 06:37.580
from the entire planet...
[Inhales sharply]

06:37.580 --> 06:39.790
starting with countries
who have the most --

06:39.790 --> 06:41.880
like the United States,
for example.

06:41.880 --> 06:43.500
That would be historic.

06:43.500 --> 06:44.210
Wouldn't you agree?

06:44.210 --> 06:45.210
Mm.

06:45.210 --> 06:48.120
Now, how about that tour?

06:48.120 --> 06:51.960
♪ Ahh, push it ♪

06:51.960 --> 06:53.960
♪ Ahh, push it ♪

06:53.960 --> 06:54.710
♪ P-Push it real good ♪

07:00.960 --> 07:01.920
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

07:01.920 --> 07:03.080
[ Footsteps approaching ]

07:03.080 --> 07:04.540
Okay, I've flagged people
on the guest list

07:04.540 --> 07:05.960
most prone to scandal.

07:05.960 --> 07:07.170
We should make sure
to hit them up tonight.

07:07.170 --> 07:08.790
They're our priority.

07:11.420 --> 07:13.960
[ Keyboard clacking ]

07:13.960 --> 07:17.080
Huck. You okay?

07:17.080 --> 07:19.880
[ Sighs ]
I don't want to go.

07:19.880 --> 07:21.380
I'm not very good at...

07:21.380 --> 07:23.120
small talk.

07:23.120 --> 07:25.120
Well, you know, you don't really
have to say much.

07:25.120 --> 07:27.880
Just ask one or two
questions,

07:27.880 --> 07:29.880
get them talking.

07:29.880 --> 07:32.750
The best way I know
how to get people talking is...

07:32.750 --> 07:34.710
is to hurt them.

07:34.710 --> 07:35.920
But you only hurt people

07:35.920 --> 07:37.790
who don't want to answer
your questions.

07:37.790 --> 07:39.250
These people tonight --

07:39.250 --> 07:40.750
they like to hear
themselves talk.

07:40.750 --> 07:43.120
And they love talking
about themselves.

07:43.120 --> 07:45.460
Ask a question,
let them talk.

07:45.460 --> 07:46.670
You'll be fine.

07:50.540 --> 07:52.750
Do you miss it?

07:52.750 --> 07:54.620
The White House?

07:54.620 --> 08:02.000
♪♪

08:02.000 --> 08:09.460
♪♪

08:09.460 --> 08:11.750
I was a big dog --

08:11.750 --> 08:14.710
effecting policy...

08:14.710 --> 08:18.290
that affected
300 million lives.

08:20.920 --> 08:23.670
I'd be lying if I said
I didn't miss it...

08:23.670 --> 08:25.500
sometimes.

08:29.380 --> 08:31.210
But, you know...

08:34.670 --> 08:38.210
...I prefer being
a gladiator.

08:38.210 --> 08:42.710
♪♪

08:42.710 --> 08:45.460
I welcomed this man
into America's house.

08:45.460 --> 08:46.920
This was a mistake.
He's unreasonable.

08:46.920 --> 08:48.580
True, but that doesn't
negate the fact that

08:48.580 --> 08:50.670
we need President Rashad
to sign this treaty.

08:50.670 --> 08:52.500
[ Sighing ] How soon
do we think Bashran

08:52.500 --> 08:54.170
can get their hands
on a nuclear weapon anyway?

08:56.830 --> 08:58.460
Thank you, Yvette.

09:01.750 --> 09:03.040
[ Door closes ]

09:03.040 --> 09:04.500
The CIA Director
estimates anywhere

09:04.500 --> 09:07.380
from five months
to a year.
That soon?

09:07.380 --> 09:10.790
Mellie, Rashad's cooperation
is imperative.

09:10.790 --> 09:12.580
Tonight's dinner
is crucial.

09:14.920 --> 09:17.380
[ Sighs ]

09:17.380 --> 09:19.170
What do you say
we skip the dinner?

09:19.170 --> 09:21.000
Go to Georgetown,
have some drinks,

09:21.000 --> 09:23.920
meet some guys.
Madam President,
if we can focus --

09:23.920 --> 09:25.540
It would be so much fun.
Think about it.

09:25.540 --> 09:26.830
I mean, it doesn't have
to be Georgetown.

09:26.830 --> 09:29.170
We can go wherever the hot
single guys in D.C.

09:29.170 --> 09:30.580
hang out nowadays.
Madam President --

09:30.580 --> 09:31.830
That is the problem --
Madam President,

09:31.830 --> 09:32.920
always Madam President.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.420
I am not complaining.

09:34.420 --> 09:36.290
I wanted to be first,
I fought to be first,

09:36.290 --> 09:38.040
and, of course,
I knew the cure for sexism

09:38.040 --> 09:39.460
would come with side effects.

09:39.460 --> 09:40.920
But, my God, Liv.

09:40.920 --> 09:42.830
It never turns off.

09:42.830 --> 09:45.380
You never stop being President,
not for one minute.

09:45.380 --> 09:46.960
It's all missiles
and treaties

09:46.960 --> 09:48.420
and worrying about
the safety of the nation

09:48.420 --> 09:50.080
every minute of the day.

09:50.080 --> 09:51.920
Olivia: You feel like you're
losing who you really are.

09:51.920 --> 09:53.120
You feel like a prisoner.

09:53.120 --> 09:54.170
You feel trapped
under the weight

09:54.170 --> 09:55.750
of the power
and the responsibility.

09:55.750 --> 09:56.790
It's crushing you.

09:56.790 --> 09:58.290
If only the world
would allow you

09:58.290 --> 10:00.830
to do this job
and still be you, right?

10:00.830 --> 10:02.540
[ Sighs deeply ]

10:02.540 --> 10:05.580
Being a woman doesn't
make you original.

10:05.580 --> 10:07.290
You sound just like Fitz,

10:07.290 --> 10:09.170
who sounded just like
every other President.

10:09.170 --> 10:10.790
But I'm not.
[ Scoffs ]

10:10.790 --> 10:12.620
I'm not just POTUS.

10:12.620 --> 10:14.330
I am Single Female POTUS.

10:14.330 --> 10:15.330
Do you know
what that means?

10:15.330 --> 10:17.460
It means I'm a human
chastity belt.

10:17.460 --> 10:18.960
Men have, historically,

10:18.960 --> 10:20.210
always had trouble
getting turned on

10:20.210 --> 10:22.040
by powerful women --
the idiots.

10:22.040 --> 10:25.080
And when that powerful woman is
the leader of the free world?

10:27.380 --> 10:31.170
Olivia, there is a famine
in my lady bits.

10:31.170 --> 10:34.380
My vagina is beautiful,
she is welcoming,

10:34.380 --> 10:35.960
but she is getting treated
like a murder house.

10:35.960 --> 10:37.120
I can't get anything
in there.
Okay!

10:37.120 --> 10:39.710
So that is a colorful visual
I did not need.

10:39.710 --> 10:41.380
You know what I need?
I need a vibrator.

10:41.380 --> 10:42.880
The President needs
a vibrator.

10:42.880 --> 10:44.580
Can I get one? No.

10:44.580 --> 10:46.000
[ Scoffs ]

10:46.000 --> 10:48.170
Can I go into a store
and buy one? No!

10:48.170 --> 10:49.380
I can't order one online.

10:49.380 --> 10:51.670
I don't have a credit card
anymore.

10:51.670 --> 10:53.880
I'm definitely not gonna ask
the military valet

10:53.880 --> 10:56.290
who attends to my personal items
to go and pick one up for me.

10:56.290 --> 10:59.290
I can't ask any staffer,
really, because,

10:59.290 --> 11:01.040
I mean,
think of the political tea

11:01.040 --> 11:01.790
the Democrats could spill.

11:01.790 --> 11:03.620
The headline --

11:03.620 --> 11:07.290
"Staffer forced to purchase
sex toys for President Grant."

11:07.290 --> 11:09.080
You want to talk about
the crown jewel

11:09.080 --> 11:10.670
of the American
prison system?

11:10.670 --> 11:14.000
I can't even smuggle an orgasm
into this place.

11:15.580 --> 11:16.830
[ Laughs ]

11:16.830 --> 11:19.830
[ Chuckles ]

11:19.830 --> 11:21.000
[ Claps hands ]

11:21.000 --> 11:22.040
[ Laughing continues ]

11:26.460 --> 11:28.790
[ Stammers ]

11:28.790 --> 11:32.040
I just keep thinking...

11:32.040 --> 11:34.750
how would Ken Burns
immortalize this moment

11:34.750 --> 11:36.540
in your documentary?

11:36.540 --> 11:37.960
[ Both laughing ]

11:42.380 --> 11:45.540
Well, I hope that
he would use a reenactment.

11:45.540 --> 11:47.790
[ Both laugh ]

11:52.250 --> 11:53.880
Oh...

11:56.540 --> 11:57.960
Ugh.

12:00.250 --> 12:02.620
[ Sighs ]

12:02.620 --> 12:04.250
It's lonely.

12:06.710 --> 12:07.830
I know.

12:10.170 --> 12:11.580
I really do know.

12:11.580 --> 12:19.580
♪♪

12:19.580 --> 12:22.000
But...

12:22.000 --> 12:25.790
this is the job.

12:25.790 --> 12:31.620
You have to do the job.

12:31.620 --> 12:34.080
I know.

12:37.540 --> 12:44.540
♪♪

12:44.540 --> 12:45.880
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:45.880 --> 12:48.880
I will work on President Rashad
at dinner.

12:48.880 --> 12:50.420
If I can't get laid,
I can, at least,

12:50.420 --> 12:52.710
do something
about nuclear proliferation.

12:52.710 --> 12:55.960
Let's go make
some world peace.

13:02.080 --> 13:03.710
One of his start-ups
is developing

13:03.710 --> 13:06.500
"insect-based
meal replacement shakes."

13:06.500 --> 13:09.790
Did you know our friend
Mr. Glackland eats bugs?

13:09.790 --> 13:11.710
Literally eats bugs.

13:18.500 --> 13:20.330
[ Sighs ]

13:33.670 --> 13:34.670
[ Keypad beeps ]

13:34.670 --> 13:36.040
[ Whirring ]

13:38.040 --> 13:39.250
Jake: Over here.

13:39.250 --> 13:40.210
[ Door closes ]

13:40.210 --> 13:41.670
What's that?

13:41.670 --> 13:45.040
This is the most important
piece of equipment we have.

13:45.040 --> 13:48.460
No B613 command center
is complete without it.

13:51.120 --> 13:52.750
Tiny pleasures.

13:52.750 --> 13:54.540
[ Mini fridge door closes ]
President Rashad.

13:54.540 --> 13:55.830
He's being difficult.

13:55.830 --> 13:57.250
Mellie's gonna work on him
at dinner.

13:57.250 --> 13:59.210
Maybe he'll soften.
I doubt he will.

13:59.210 --> 14:00.330
If he doesn't,
we're going to need

14:00.330 --> 14:02.120
a little help
getting our treaty signed.

14:02.120 --> 14:03.290
A little help.
We're talking about --

14:03.290 --> 14:05.170
Dirt --
Hold him upside down,

14:05.170 --> 14:08.330
see what falls out
of his pockets.

14:08.330 --> 14:10.120
Think you can do that?

14:10.120 --> 14:13.420
Absolutely.

14:13.420 --> 14:16.620
This was the only place
he felt free, you know.

14:16.620 --> 14:18.500
FDR --
the guy who built this place.

14:18.500 --> 14:20.460
Outside, he was confined
to a wheelchair,

14:20.460 --> 14:23.500
but in here....
in the water,

14:23.500 --> 14:26.080
it's like he could fly.

14:26.080 --> 14:28.580
Hard to believe now,
isn't it?

14:28.580 --> 14:31.500
Let me know when
you've found something.

14:31.500 --> 14:33.170
[ Keypad beeps, door opens ]

14:37.420 --> 14:43.210
[ Newcleus' "Jam On It" plays ]

14:43.210 --> 14:45.210
[ Laughs ]

14:45.210 --> 14:46.620
♪ Yeah ♪

14:46.620 --> 14:49.620
♪♪

14:49.620 --> 14:51.460
♪ Jam on it ♪

14:51.460 --> 14:53.040
♪ Yeah, yeah, we know, we know ♪
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

14:53.040 --> 14:54.790
♪ Huh ♪

14:54.790 --> 14:57.380
Cyrus: They say you can
see the castle from every hole,

14:57.380 --> 15:00.170
but I can only attest
to the view from the sand trap.

15:00.170 --> 15:01.210
[ Laughter ]

15:01.210 --> 15:03.500
In life,
as it is in golf.

15:03.500 --> 15:05.000
Excuse me, I, uh...
can't take another minute.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.080
I beg your pardon.
Fenton Glackland.

15:07.080 --> 15:08.420
I'd say
I'm at your service,

15:08.420 --> 15:09.960
but considering
the amount of money I've given,

15:09.960 --> 15:11.710
I think you're technically
at mine.

15:11.710 --> 15:15.120
Mr. Glackland.

15:15.120 --> 15:17.920
Your reputation
precedes you.

15:17.920 --> 15:19.790
Oh, it's only sugar.

15:19.790 --> 15:21.380
Passed a churro cart
on the drive over,

15:21.380 --> 15:23.920
and I couldn't resist.
Oh, a churro cart?

15:23.920 --> 15:26.620
You realize the chef tonight
has three Michelin stars.

15:26.620 --> 15:27.500
And well-deserved --

15:27.500 --> 15:28.750
I've eaten at
all her restaurants.

15:28.750 --> 15:31.080
But her portions?
Insulting.

15:31.080 --> 15:32.210
If you're
the least bit hungry,

15:32.210 --> 15:34.380
I suggest, uh...
filling up on apps.

15:35.830 --> 15:38.500
Woman: Truly, I'd assumed that
the firm had closed its doors

15:38.500 --> 15:40.080
when Olivia Pope left
for the White House.

15:40.080 --> 15:42.290
Unfortunately,
that's a popular misconception,

15:42.290 --> 15:44.080
and one we're eager
to correct.

15:44.080 --> 15:45.710
Stuffed date, my dear?
Ooh!

15:45.710 --> 15:47.210
What a gentleman.

15:47.210 --> 15:49.460
Tell me, how long have
the two of you been married?

15:49.460 --> 15:52.250
Oh, actually, we're --
We're about a year and half in,
right, Kevin?

15:52.250 --> 15:53.580
Right. Year and a half.

15:53.580 --> 15:56.540
I found a poodle
on the side of the road once.

15:56.540 --> 15:59.000
I tried to massage its heart
and keep it alive --

15:59.000 --> 16:00.170
didn't work.

16:00.170 --> 16:02.790
Thank you,
thank you, thank you.

16:02.790 --> 16:04.500
Our next three lunches
are on me.

16:04.500 --> 16:05.880
How does that math work?

16:05.880 --> 16:07.380
It should be at least one lunch
for every ticket.

16:07.380 --> 16:09.710
Hey! You already had
the plus-one.

16:09.710 --> 16:11.620
You wouldn't really make
your date pay for her own meal,

16:11.620 --> 16:12.830
would you?

16:12.830 --> 16:14.250
No.
No, I suppose not.

16:14.250 --> 16:16.580
♪♪

16:16.580 --> 16:19.080
You know, I think
I see Senator Powell over there.

16:19.080 --> 16:20.000
I should go say hello.

16:22.750 --> 16:24.920
What happened?
She didn't want to talk.

16:24.920 --> 16:25.880
I told you,
I'm not good at this.

16:25.880 --> 16:27.290
Try talking to someone

16:27.290 --> 16:29.420
you might have something
in common with, like...

16:29.420 --> 16:31.170
There are lots of military
people here.

16:31.170 --> 16:32.420
Try one of them.

16:32.420 --> 16:35.250
♪♪

16:35.250 --> 16:36.880
Quinn: Liv.

16:36.880 --> 16:39.380
Quinn. You're here.
You're all here.

16:39.380 --> 16:40.960
Yes, we are,
but I don't want you to worry.

16:40.960 --> 16:42.290
We're not going
to embarrass you.

16:42.290 --> 16:44.380
Huck is on the leash,
this baby is staying in,

16:44.380 --> 16:46.120
so no broken water
on this very nice carpet.

16:46.120 --> 16:47.790
And Charlie isn't
even Charlie.

16:47.790 --> 16:48.920
He's Kevin.

16:48.920 --> 16:50.540
Oh. Great.

16:52.830 --> 16:54.830
Give me a sec, okay?

16:54.830 --> 16:55.920
What are you doing here?

16:55.920 --> 16:57.210
I was invited here.

16:57.210 --> 16:58.380
You know Sarah Jacobi?
She works at Defense --

16:58.380 --> 17:00.620
You need to leave.
That would be rude to Sarah.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.460
If you're here trying
to make some ridiculous point --

17:02.460 --> 17:04.420
No, I'm here trying
to ridiculously impress my date.

17:04.420 --> 17:05.420
You want to meet her?
She's great --

17:05.420 --> 17:07.000
She's smart,
and, get this,

17:07.000 --> 17:08.580
she doesn't even have
an assistant.

17:08.580 --> 17:09.460
Happy for you.

17:09.460 --> 17:10.750
You don't look happy.

17:10.750 --> 17:12.710
I don't have time for this.

17:12.710 --> 17:13.830
Right.

17:13.830 --> 17:15.670
Very busy, I know.

17:15.670 --> 17:17.290
[ Fanfare plays ]

17:17.290 --> 17:18.790
Announcer:
Ladies and gentlemen,

17:18.790 --> 17:21.330
the President
of the United States

17:21.330 --> 17:26.710
accompanied
by President Rashad of Bashran.

17:26.710 --> 17:28.080
[ "Hail to the Chief" plays ]

17:28.080 --> 17:30.080
[ Camera shutters clicking ]
[ Applause ]

17:36.920 --> 17:38.830
And may this evening
begin a new era

17:38.830 --> 17:41.830
of peace and prosperity
for Bashran,

17:41.830 --> 17:45.460
and a friendship which endures
well beyond our time.

17:50.750 --> 17:52.830
Kind words
from an elegant host.

17:52.830 --> 17:55.040
Kind words from a President
with a clear agenda,

17:55.040 --> 17:56.920
one that is your country's
best interest.

17:56.920 --> 17:57.830
Your best interest,
perhaps.

17:57.830 --> 17:59.210
I'm trying to avoid

17:59.210 --> 18:00.540
a large-scale war
in the Middle East.

18:00.540 --> 18:01.830
You're trying
to put a feather in your cap

18:01.830 --> 18:03.210
and get a political win.

18:03.210 --> 18:05.500
Securing a nuclear treaty
would be an achievement

18:05.500 --> 18:07.830
far beyond feathers
in our respective caps.

18:07.830 --> 18:09.250
What you're seeking
you don't want,

18:09.250 --> 18:10.000
I assure you.

18:10.000 --> 18:11.460
[ Sighs ]

18:11.460 --> 18:13.250
We have an expression
in this country.

18:13.250 --> 18:16.290
It's called
"mansplaining."

18:16.290 --> 18:18.080
If I agree to this
treaty of yours,

18:18.080 --> 18:19.620
I'll be considered weak.

18:19.620 --> 18:21.830
Support for the well-funded,
well-trained radicals

18:21.830 --> 18:23.880
who want me out of power
will grow.

18:23.880 --> 18:25.460
I'll be exiled at best

18:25.460 --> 18:27.380
and assassinated at worst,

18:27.380 --> 18:29.500
and instead of dealing with me,
you'll be dealing

18:29.500 --> 18:31.830
with a hornets nest
of anti-American goons

18:31.830 --> 18:34.120
with access
to radioactive materials.

18:34.120 --> 18:35.380
We can help you sell
the idea of peace

18:35.380 --> 18:36.380
to your people.

18:36.380 --> 18:37.670
I can make visit
to your country...

18:37.670 --> 18:39.250
[ Scoffs ]
...talk to --

18:39.250 --> 18:41.040
The godless white lady
coming to save us?

18:41.040 --> 18:42.380
I don't think so.

18:42.380 --> 18:45.120
Maybe if they got
to know me better?

18:45.120 --> 18:46.540
You have a fair point.

18:46.540 --> 18:49.080
You charm and intelligence
are powerful weapons.

18:49.080 --> 18:51.210
I can see that now.

18:51.210 --> 18:53.170
But I'm afraid
they're not enough.

18:53.170 --> 18:55.750
Let me mansplain more.

18:55.750 --> 18:58.960
Like I said, the moment I say
the word "treaty,"

18:58.960 --> 19:00.920
I'm either dead or exiled,

19:00.920 --> 19:03.670
especially now that Dakal
is developing its own weapons

19:03.670 --> 19:06.460
right next door.

19:06.460 --> 19:11.670
So I'm afraid your dream
is thwarted by my reality.

19:11.670 --> 19:13.080
[ Sighs ]

19:15.080 --> 19:20.000
♪♪

19:20.000 --> 19:22.540
Please tell me
you've got something.

19:22.540 --> 19:25.290
Our friend
likes 'em young.

19:25.290 --> 19:27.000
That girl can't be
older than 16.

19:27.000 --> 19:28.170
When were these taken?

19:28.170 --> 19:30.040
Last night at the Embassy.

19:30.040 --> 19:32.170
Rashad's security detail
snuck her in the back.

19:32.170 --> 19:33.750
Any photos inside
the bedroom,

19:33.750 --> 19:35.380
proof that
money exchanged hands?

19:35.380 --> 19:37.000
Nothing I caught
on camera.
Keep looking.

19:37.000 --> 19:40.290
In Bashran, sexual deviants are
either imprisoned or executed.

19:40.290 --> 19:41.880
My guess,
he'd rather sign a treaty

19:41.880 --> 19:44.460
than be dragged from his palace
and hung from a crane.

19:44.460 --> 19:47.420
Your wish is my command,
boss.

19:47.420 --> 19:50.460
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:50.460 --> 19:59.750
♪♪

20:06.290 --> 20:08.580
-Coffee?
-None for me. Thank you.
-I will, thanks.

20:08.580 --> 20:10.250
You know, Congressman, it's
so funny you mentioned polo.

20:10.250 --> 20:12.290
My husband's family
are mad for the game.

20:12.290 --> 20:13.500
Isn't that right, Kevin?

20:13.500 --> 20:15.040
-Indeed. Quite mad.
-Really?

20:15.040 --> 20:17.080
You're not related
to the Atlanta Dunwoodys,

20:17.080 --> 20:18.920
are you?
Um...no.

20:18.920 --> 20:21.210
Kevin's family's
all California based --

20:21.210 --> 20:24.170
Stanford alumns,
the lot of them.

20:24.170 --> 20:25.540
You know, I'm told Santa Barbara
has a lovely polo club.

20:25.540 --> 20:26.880
Mm.

20:26.880 --> 20:28.540
[ Indistinct chatter ]

20:28.540 --> 20:31.000
Yeah, but the 1911 is
the best sidearm ever built.

20:31.000 --> 20:32.580
It won two world wars.

20:32.580 --> 20:35.170
New war, new weapon -- the M9
is more resistant to sand.

20:35.170 --> 20:36.250
And it's a lot cheaper.

20:36.250 --> 20:37.420
Yeah,
certainly doesn't hurt, right?

20:37.420 --> 20:38.830
[ Laughs, snorts ]

20:41.170 --> 20:43.000
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

20:43.000 --> 20:45.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:45.750 --> 20:47.710
You, uh...served?

20:49.960 --> 20:51.380
I don't know.

20:51.380 --> 20:53.580
You don't know
if you've served?

20:53.580 --> 20:55.170
Is that baklava?

20:59.920 --> 21:01.620
What'd I tell you?
Chintzy.

21:01.620 --> 21:04.120
She should skip the gold leaf
and double the saffron foam.

21:07.460 --> 21:09.380
I'm embarrassing you.
Not at all.

21:09.380 --> 21:12.580
I'm eager to know how the cake
fared against the churros.

21:12.580 --> 21:14.670
[ Exhales sharply ]
You know what I did today?

21:14.670 --> 21:17.580
Invented a hovercraft
powered by cockroach parts?

21:17.580 --> 21:20.920
I bought a Cèzanne --
$105 million.

21:20.920 --> 21:23.330
Well, ducky for you.

21:23.330 --> 21:24.830
Which Cèzanne?

21:24.830 --> 21:26.420
I don't remember.

21:26.420 --> 21:28.380
But my buyer assures me
it's quite famous --

21:28.380 --> 21:30.170
a boy, a vest --
something like that.

21:30.170 --> 21:31.380
"The Boy in the Red Vest"?

21:31.380 --> 21:33.170
Yeah, that sounds right.

21:33.170 --> 21:35.460
That's...

21:35.460 --> 21:38.710
one of his most...

21:38.710 --> 21:42.080
You spent $100 million
on a painting,

21:42.080 --> 21:44.670
and you don't even know
what painting it is?

21:44.670 --> 21:46.670
It's for my office.

21:46.670 --> 21:51.540
You see, my businesses earn
over $1 million an hour.

21:51.540 --> 21:53.880
That's over
$17,000 a minute.

21:53.880 --> 21:58.540
So there's nothing I hate more
than people wasting my time.

21:58.540 --> 22:01.210
But I found a solution.

22:01.210 --> 22:03.580
A billion dollars
of artwork

22:03.580 --> 22:05.540
hangs in the foyer
of my office --

22:05.540 --> 22:09.080
Warhol, Picasso, Monet,
soon this Cèzanne.

22:09.080 --> 22:11.790
After people walk
past all that,

22:11.790 --> 22:13.250
they tend to get right
to the point.

22:13.250 --> 22:14.750
Mm-hmm.
Which is how I like it.

22:14.750 --> 22:16.750
I can imagine.
The problem is,

22:16.750 --> 22:20.420
what good is that collection
when I'm out here in the world?

22:20.420 --> 22:23.420
You see, we've been
at this dinner nearly two hours,

22:23.420 --> 22:27.330
and you still have not asked me
why I am here.

22:27.330 --> 22:29.380
Mr. Glackland,
why are you here?

22:29.380 --> 22:31.080
Because I like to work
with experts,

22:31.080 --> 22:33.830
and you're an expert
in politics.

22:33.830 --> 22:36.460
The real expert's sitting
at the head table.

22:36.460 --> 22:38.080
I'm the one who rode
in the sidecar,

22:38.080 --> 22:40.040
went to prison, then lost.

22:40.040 --> 22:41.420
Oh. Don't sell
yourself short.

22:41.420 --> 22:42.960
You've seen it all,

22:42.960 --> 22:44.000
played every angle,

22:44.000 --> 22:44.790
seen every mistake.

22:44.790 --> 22:46.880
Okay, I'm an expert.

22:46.880 --> 22:48.080
What do you want to know?

22:49.790 --> 22:52.790
If I wanted to run
for governor...

22:52.790 --> 22:54.170
where, exactly,

22:54.170 --> 22:55.710
would I start?

22:55.710 --> 22:56.620
[ Scoffs ]

22:56.620 --> 22:58.420
Governor.

22:58.420 --> 23:01.880
You want to run
for Governor.

23:01.880 --> 23:02.920
Announcer: Ladies and gentlemen,

23:02.920 --> 23:04.540
with our dinner service
complete,

23:04.540 --> 23:06.790
we would like to invite you all
to join us in the East Room

23:06.790 --> 23:08.080
for a musical performance.

23:08.080 --> 23:10.120
No, no, no.
We're not going there.

23:10.120 --> 23:11.670
You're giving me
the private tour.

23:11.670 --> 23:13.460
Forced music appreciation?

23:13.460 --> 23:14.460
[ Groans ]

23:25.670 --> 23:27.040
Hold the performance.

23:29.000 --> 23:30.330
You want the good news first
or the bad news?

23:30.330 --> 23:32.540
Jake --
She's not a prostitute.

23:32.540 --> 23:34.830
That's the bad news.

23:34.830 --> 23:36.120
What's the good news?

23:44.250 --> 23:45.580
You can corroborate this?

23:48.880 --> 23:51.620
[ Faucet running ]

23:51.620 --> 23:53.290
[ Faucet stops ]

23:53.290 --> 23:54.830
[ Door closes,
footsteps approach ]

23:54.830 --> 23:56.250
Is the performance
about to begin?

23:56.250 --> 23:57.250
Not quite.

24:00.830 --> 24:03.080
You'll forgive
the intrusion.

24:03.080 --> 24:05.420
I felt it was best
we spoke privately.

24:09.540 --> 24:11.620
Her name is
Yasmeen Talebi.

24:11.620 --> 24:13.080
That's what
the Admissions Office

24:13.080 --> 24:14.420
at Dartmouth thinks,
anyway.

24:14.420 --> 24:16.380
What they don't know,
but you do

24:16.380 --> 24:18.540
is that her name
is Yasmeen Rashad,

24:18.540 --> 24:21.920
daughter of Amir Rashad,
your late brother.

24:21.920 --> 24:25.750
I'm told she's a...
English major

24:25.750 --> 24:28.000
with a minor
in Gender Studies.

24:28.000 --> 24:32.250
I don't imagine that would
go over very well in Bashran.

24:32.250 --> 24:33.880
Neither do you,
I'm assuming.

24:33.880 --> 24:38.380
If you did, you wouldn't
have changed her name.

24:38.380 --> 24:40.210
Mr. President...

24:40.210 --> 24:43.790
actions speak louder
than words.

24:43.790 --> 24:46.620
You may preach
nationalism,

24:46.620 --> 24:48.880
rail in your speeches
against the corrosive effect

24:48.880 --> 24:50.620
of the West on your values,

24:50.620 --> 24:53.250
but sending your niece
to the States,

24:53.250 --> 24:54.960
enrolling her
in a prestigious college

24:54.960 --> 24:56.880
under an assumed name,
offering her a future

24:56.880 --> 24:59.250
she wouldn't
otherwise have at home --

24:59.250 --> 25:01.710
that tells me who you are,
who you really are --

25:01.710 --> 25:03.120
your character.

25:03.120 --> 25:05.750
There are some
in your country

25:05.750 --> 25:08.170
who want to drag the world
back to the 12th century.

25:08.170 --> 25:09.540
Don't let them do that.

25:09.540 --> 25:10.880
Sign the treaty.

25:10.880 --> 25:14.080
Do for your country
what you've done for your niece.

25:17.880 --> 25:20.120
You're right, Ms. Pope.

25:20.120 --> 25:22.830
Actions do speak louder
than words.

25:22.830 --> 25:25.290
And this...

25:25.290 --> 25:27.750
This tells me that your country
is still sticking its nose

25:27.750 --> 25:30.000
where it doesn't belong.
Mr. President --

25:30.000 --> 25:34.250
Ambassador Marashi
warned me about you.

25:34.250 --> 25:36.080
"Watch out for Olivia Pope,"
he said.

25:36.080 --> 25:37.500
"She's the devil."

25:37.500 --> 25:40.170
Don't let your pride
get in the way of progress.

25:40.170 --> 25:42.750
You threatened his child...

25:42.750 --> 25:44.420
his son.

25:44.420 --> 25:46.000
That tells me everything
I need to know

25:46.000 --> 25:49.330
about your character.

25:49.330 --> 25:51.620
So you can forget about
your treaty.

25:51.620 --> 25:54.790
My staff and I will
be leaving immediately
after the performance.

25:54.790 --> 25:55.920
You're making a mistake.

25:55.920 --> 25:58.710
Good evening, Ms. Pope.

25:58.710 --> 26:00.330
[ Door opens ]

26:00.330 --> 26:02.170
[ Door closes ]

26:02.170 --> 26:05.540
♪♪

26:11.580 --> 26:13.290
Fenton: So, I said to myself,

26:13.290 --> 26:14.880
if there's this much
waste in San Francisco,
imagine at the state level.

26:14.880 --> 26:16.380
I mean, their systems
are obsolete.

26:16.380 --> 26:18.670
Plus, I'm running
out of companies to found.

26:18.670 --> 26:20.170
[ Chuckles ]

26:20.170 --> 26:21.670
I saved the best for last.

26:21.670 --> 26:24.710
Oh. Of course.

26:24.710 --> 26:27.170
This is it?

26:27.170 --> 26:31.250
The seat of power,
the center of the known world.

26:31.250 --> 26:33.420
Yeah.

26:33.420 --> 26:36.710
[ Chuckling ] Not what
you expected, huh?

26:36.710 --> 26:38.380
Well, it's a little --

26:38.380 --> 26:41.210
a little smaller
than I thought.

26:41.210 --> 26:43.330
But I guess people
were stunted

26:43.330 --> 26:45.540
by calcium deficiency
back in...

26:45.540 --> 26:48.580
1909.
We don't really let people...

26:49.790 --> 26:50.920
Oh...

26:50.920 --> 26:52.420
you know...

26:52.420 --> 26:54.540
[ Exhales sharply ]

26:54.540 --> 26:57.120
I could get used to this.

26:57.120 --> 26:59.080
Screw governor.

26:59.080 --> 27:02.580
Maybe I should drop a few mil
and make a bid for Prez.

27:05.670 --> 27:08.460
Get up.

27:08.460 --> 27:10.080
Get up!

27:13.460 --> 27:15.420
You -- [ Stammering ]

27:15.420 --> 27:17.210
Boob!

27:17.210 --> 27:21.000
You ignorant, entitled...

27:21.000 --> 27:22.580
[ Breathing heavily ]

27:22.580 --> 27:28.580
This is the most venerated
office in the country --

27:28.580 --> 27:31.960
The democracy that defined
modern democracy.

27:31.960 --> 27:36.540
The chance to sit at this desk
is an honor and a privilege,

27:36.540 --> 27:38.830
not some Cracker Jack prize
that gets handed out

27:38.830 --> 27:41.210
to any Forbes 100 upstart

27:41.210 --> 27:45.580
who can "drop a few mil"
when they're getting bored.

27:45.580 --> 27:47.580
FYI, that Cèzanne
that you bought

27:47.580 --> 27:49.460
just to prove to everyone
how important you are?

27:49.460 --> 27:50.670
[ Exhales sharply ]

27:50.670 --> 27:53.000
It's worth all that money
for a reason.

27:53.000 --> 27:55.330
Cèzanne's work shaped

27:55.330 --> 27:57.040
the next half-century
of modern art.

27:57.040 --> 27:58.080
But you don't care.

27:58.080 --> 28:01.580
You can't even pretend to care,

28:01.580 --> 28:03.420
which is why you'll never
win an election,

28:03.420 --> 28:04.620
certainly not for Governor.

28:04.620 --> 28:05.670
And for President?

28:05.670 --> 28:08.170
Don't make me laugh!

28:15.460 --> 28:17.460
So, it's time
to call it a day.

28:23.670 --> 28:26.080
I'm leaving.

28:26.080 --> 28:27.580
I'm s-- so sorry.

28:27.580 --> 28:29.170
Mr. Glackland, the Oval --

28:29.170 --> 28:31.710
it's very close to my heart.

28:31.710 --> 28:35.960
[ Piano plays ]

28:35.960 --> 28:39.960
♪ Summer soft ♪

28:39.960 --> 28:44.330
♪ Wakes you up with a kiss
to start the morning off ♪

28:44.330 --> 28:48.330
♪ In the midst of herself
playing Santa Claus ♪

28:48.330 --> 28:55.670
♪ She brings gifts
through her breeze ♪

28:55.670 --> 28:58.080
♪ Morning rain ♪

28:58.080 --> 29:02.290
♪ Gently plays her rhythms
on the window pane ♪

29:02.290 --> 29:03.500
There you are.

29:03.500 --> 29:04.420
Here I am.

29:04.420 --> 29:05.710
I thought
you might've left.

29:05.710 --> 29:07.620
Mm.
I've been networking --

29:07.620 --> 29:10.000
haven't had
a moment to breathe.

29:10.000 --> 29:11.880
Now's your moment.

29:11.880 --> 29:13.040
[ Sighs ]

29:13.040 --> 29:15.080
I love this song.

29:15.080 --> 29:17.670
♪ ...to see what she'll do ♪

29:17.670 --> 29:22.500
♪ Is it sun or rain for you ♪

29:22.500 --> 29:26.330
♪ But it breaks your heart
in two ♪

29:26.330 --> 29:31.330
♪ When you find it's October ♪

29:31.330 --> 29:36.000
♪ And she's gone ♪

29:36.000 --> 29:40.330
♪ And she's gone ♪

29:40.330 --> 29:45.080
♪ Summer's gone ♪

29:45.080 --> 29:49.540
♪ You've been fooled by April ♪

29:49.540 --> 29:52.170
We are doing so well,
I feel like celebrating.

29:52.170 --> 29:53.830
Oh! Do you think they have
any of that cake left?

29:53.830 --> 29:55.330
Do you want me to look?

29:55.330 --> 29:56.620
Because that sounds like a job
for your husband.

29:56.620 --> 29:57.620
Kevin.
What?

29:57.620 --> 30:00.080
Never mind.

30:00.080 --> 30:01.210
I thought he was Kevin.

30:01.210 --> 30:02.830
He is.
[ Sighs ]

30:02.830 --> 30:04.790
Everyone is acting
so weird tonight.

30:04.790 --> 30:08.210
♪♪

30:08.210 --> 30:09.920
Huck,
We need you in there, man.

30:09.920 --> 30:11.880
The evening's almost over.

30:11.880 --> 30:13.380
[ Sighs ] Come on.

30:13.380 --> 30:14.500
You were hitting it off

30:14.500 --> 30:15.750
with that one Army guy,
weren't you?

30:15.750 --> 30:17.250
I was...

30:17.250 --> 30:18.380
till I saw
his service medals.

30:18.380 --> 30:20.040
And, what, too many
medals of valor?

30:20.040 --> 30:21.290
They were in the wrong order.

30:21.290 --> 30:22.880
They're supposed to be
in order of precedence --

30:22.880 --> 30:24.920
personal awards first,
then unit awards,

30:24.920 --> 30:26.040
then non-military awards,
then --

30:26.040 --> 30:28.120
Huck, get to the point.

30:28.120 --> 30:29.880
I don't think
he's actually in the Army.

30:29.880 --> 30:31.380
I snuck a picture of him,

30:31.380 --> 30:32.670
and I'm running it through
the military database now.

30:32.670 --> 30:34.670
Wait, didn't they take
your phone at the door?

30:34.670 --> 30:35.710
Yeah.
Then how did you --

30:35.710 --> 30:36.540
Why? You need one?

30:36.540 --> 30:37.670
Forget it.

30:37.670 --> 30:39.670
So, who is this guy?

30:39.670 --> 30:40.830
I don't know.

30:40.830 --> 30:43.380
But he's never been
in the Army,

30:43.380 --> 30:45.250
which means he's not
who he says he is.

30:45.250 --> 30:46.790
So?
Neither are you and Charlie.

30:46.790 --> 30:48.500
[ Scoffs ] Yeah.

30:48.500 --> 30:50.710
Because we're a couple
of killers.

30:50.710 --> 30:58.750
♪ Oooooh ♪

30:58.750 --> 31:02.250
[ Applause ]

31:10.250 --> 31:11.710
[ Chuckles ]

31:11.710 --> 31:13.960
Looked like a hasty exit
by the Bashranis.

31:13.960 --> 31:15.830
Do you think that's gonna impact
pending negotiations?

31:15.830 --> 31:17.250
Where's your date?
Where's Sarah?

31:17.250 --> 31:18.380
You're changing
the subject.

31:18.380 --> 31:19.830
Don't make me have you
escorted out of here.

31:19.830 --> 31:21.790
That would cause
quite a scene.

31:21.790 --> 31:23.670
Also, can you imagine
tomorrow morning's news cycle?

31:23.670 --> 31:25.330
Journalist gets kicked out
of state dinner

31:25.330 --> 31:26.290
for just doing his job.

31:26.290 --> 31:27.670
Oh, so this is
your job now?

31:27.670 --> 31:29.580
This is you with your
journalistic hat on now?

31:29.580 --> 31:31.420
President Rashad didn't
just leave here

31:31.420 --> 31:33.460
because he wanted to be in bed
by 8:00, Olivia.

31:33.460 --> 31:34.380
Something happened.

31:34.380 --> 31:36.000
This is me
doing you a solid.

31:36.000 --> 31:37.460
I'm giving you a chance
to make a comment

31:37.460 --> 31:39.620
for a story I'm running with
in eight hours.

31:39.620 --> 31:41.040
There is no story here,
Curtis.

31:41.040 --> 31:42.170
The state dinner is over.

31:42.170 --> 31:43.790
Guests typically leave
when it's over.

31:43.790 --> 31:45.040
Big surprise.

31:46.580 --> 31:47.960
What?

31:47.960 --> 31:49.540
Nothing --
It's your knack for spin.

31:49.540 --> 31:50.920
It is astounding.

31:50.920 --> 31:52.790
It's not spin.
It's the truth.

31:52.790 --> 31:54.080
Do you even know
the difference anymore?

31:54.080 --> 31:55.420
[ Scoffs ]
Whether it's acting like

31:55.420 --> 31:57.290
you don't know
what's going down at this dinner

31:57.290 --> 31:59.710
or pretending like [Hushed]
you're okay with scheduling

31:59.710 --> 32:01.880
our little hotel room meet-ups
through your assistant.

32:01.880 --> 32:04.790
You are all about spin.

32:04.790 --> 32:07.540
Be real with me, Olivia.

32:07.540 --> 32:08.670
Or are you afraid
of doing that, too?

32:08.670 --> 32:09.750
You don't know the first thing
about me.

32:09.750 --> 32:11.710
Maybe I don't.

32:11.710 --> 32:13.040
But I'd like to.

32:16.580 --> 32:17.830
Abby: Liv.

32:17.830 --> 32:19.920
We have a problem.

32:24.080 --> 32:25.920
President Rashad.

32:25.920 --> 32:28.290
Uh, President Grant sent me
to stop you.

32:28.290 --> 32:29.790
She wants to talk,
one-on-one.

32:29.790 --> 32:31.620
I don't know you.

32:31.620 --> 32:33.750
She thought it best to keep
her advisers out of it.

32:33.750 --> 32:35.540
She said
you'd understand why.

32:38.500 --> 32:39.710
Wait here.

32:39.710 --> 32:40.880
This way, Mr. President.

32:47.380 --> 32:48.080
[ Lock engages ]

32:50.540 --> 32:52.290
[ Gun cocks ]

32:52.290 --> 32:54.080
♪♪

32:54.080 --> 32:55.620
[ Sighs ]

32:55.620 --> 32:56.960
First you spy on me,

32:56.960 --> 33:00.000
then you blackmail me,
and when that doesn't work.

33:00.000 --> 33:02.290
you assassinate me
in your own house?

33:02.290 --> 33:04.290
Do you Americans
have no shame?

33:04.290 --> 33:06.170
Do you?

33:06.170 --> 33:07.880
Worrying about
the Americans

33:07.880 --> 33:11.120
when your concern should be
for your people,

33:11.120 --> 33:13.710
groveling
for their approval...

33:13.710 --> 33:16.000
while your own country burns.

33:16.000 --> 33:17.620
You're Bashrani.

33:17.620 --> 33:18.540
[ Speaks Farsi ]

33:18.540 --> 33:21.620
♪♪

33:21.620 --> 33:23.710
[ Speaks Farsi ]

33:23.710 --> 33:32.790
♪♪

33:32.790 --> 33:34.580
Threat neutralized.

33:34.580 --> 33:36.080
[ Men grunting ]

33:36.080 --> 33:37.920
♪♪

33:37.920 --> 33:39.880
I'm fine. I'm fine!

33:39.880 --> 33:46.210
♪♪

33:46.210 --> 33:47.170
[ Sighs ]

33:54.380 --> 33:56.000
The NSA will be coordinating
with your team directly,
President Rashad.

33:56.000 --> 33:57.830
We'll find out how the
assassin got into the dinner
and who he's working for.

33:57.830 --> 33:59.500
-The moment you find something.
-You'll be the first to know.

34:03.540 --> 34:04.960
I already know
who's behind this.

34:04.960 --> 34:07.120
The radicals in my country
have been trying to force me

34:07.120 --> 34:08.330
to bend to their will
for months.

34:08.330 --> 34:09.750
But now they've shown
their true desire --

34:09.750 --> 34:11.380
to kill me.

34:11.380 --> 34:14.540
They may fail today,
but tomorrow...

34:14.540 --> 34:16.210
[ Liquid pours ]
Mr. President,
we're here to help.

34:16.210 --> 34:17.920
If there's anything more
we can do --

34:17.920 --> 34:19.620
anything.

34:19.620 --> 34:22.000
Olivia, could you give
the President and me a moment,

34:22.000 --> 34:23.540
please?

34:23.540 --> 34:26.170
Of course,
Madam President.

34:28.750 --> 34:30.330
[ Door opens, closes ]

34:30.330 --> 34:33.330
Your fears are by no means
unfounded.

34:33.330 --> 34:35.380
I know them
all too well myself.

34:35.380 --> 34:36.790
[ Inhales sharply ]
Four to six

34:36.790 --> 34:39.330
are the magic numbers
around here.

34:39.330 --> 34:40.790
Four to six
credible death threats

34:40.790 --> 34:42.540
are lodged against me
every single day,

34:42.540 --> 34:44.750
according to my friends
at the Secret Service.

34:44.750 --> 34:46.540
Those fears...

34:46.540 --> 34:47.920
They come with the job.

34:47.920 --> 34:49.040
You think
I'm afraid of dying?

34:49.040 --> 34:51.250
I didn't --
Failure, Madam President,

34:51.250 --> 34:53.750
is more terrifying than
any possible fate.

34:53.750 --> 34:56.290
Failing my people,
leaving them behind,

34:56.290 --> 34:58.460
hopeless and weak
before I can finish,

34:58.460 --> 35:02.790
bestowing upon them a lifetime
of discord and anarchy --

35:02.790 --> 35:05.540
That's what I fear.

35:05.540 --> 35:07.420
Not death.

35:07.420 --> 35:11.580
Then you have the opportunity,
Mr. President, right now,

35:11.580 --> 35:12.750
to make sure that
that never happens.

35:12.750 --> 35:14.170
Your treaty.

35:14.170 --> 35:15.540
Our treaty.

35:15.540 --> 35:16.670
It's not that simple.

35:16.670 --> 35:18.210
It could be.

35:18.210 --> 35:20.120
[ Sighs ]

35:20.120 --> 35:22.380
It could be your
greatest achievement.

35:22.380 --> 35:24.670
Ensuring a better future
for your country?

35:24.670 --> 35:26.790
You do that,

35:26.790 --> 35:28.620
and it sounds to me
like you don't have anything

35:28.620 --> 35:30.750
to be afraid of anymore.

35:35.920 --> 35:38.920
[ Exhales sharply ]

35:38.920 --> 35:40.960
I would need
an assurance --

35:40.960 --> 35:41.880
one, in particular.

35:41.880 --> 35:42.580
Name it.

35:42.580 --> 35:44.040
Dakal --

35:44.040 --> 35:46.250
My country's
most aggressive enemy.

35:46.250 --> 35:49.040
If I'm to sign this treaty,
then they have to do the same.

35:49.040 --> 35:51.330
If not, it's pointless.

35:51.330 --> 35:53.290
We'll bring Dakal
to the table, then.

35:53.290 --> 35:54.080
Leave that to me.

35:57.880 --> 35:59.830
Madam President,

35:59.830 --> 36:01.580
do you have something...

36:01.580 --> 36:03.880
stronger?

36:03.880 --> 36:07.460
Oh, uh...[ Laughs ]

36:07.460 --> 36:10.330
I would've offered,
but I assumed you didn't drink.

36:10.330 --> 36:12.040
It's an old habit
from university days.

36:12.040 --> 36:13.290
[ Liquid pours ]
I try to keep it
discreet.

36:13.290 --> 36:15.500
[ Chuckles ]

36:18.460 --> 36:19.380
No fun to drink alone.

36:26.880 --> 36:29.380
[ Both exhale sharply ]

36:29.380 --> 36:31.290
I assume, um...

36:31.290 --> 36:33.790
Ms. Pope has told you
about Yasmeen.

36:33.790 --> 36:34.670
Your niece.

36:34.670 --> 36:36.330
She has a picture of you

36:36.330 --> 36:38.420
hanging on the wall
of her dorm room.

36:38.420 --> 36:39.830
[ Chuckles ]

36:39.830 --> 36:41.380
She calls you...

36:41.380 --> 36:44.000
an inspiration.

36:44.000 --> 36:46.790
I wanted her to know that
her future's not limited

36:46.790 --> 36:50.250
by the traditions and laws
of her old country,

36:50.250 --> 36:52.120
that she can be anything
she wants to be.

36:52.120 --> 36:53.750
You certainly don't need
to explain --

36:53.750 --> 36:55.750
You are...

36:55.750 --> 36:58.460
extraordinary.

36:58.460 --> 37:01.710
It's an honor sitting here,
next to you, right now.

37:09.670 --> 37:10.620
[ Sighs ]

37:10.620 --> 37:12.920
I should go.

37:12.920 --> 37:13.960
[ Glass clinks ]

37:18.420 --> 37:19.790
I...

37:19.790 --> 37:22.750
look forward to the two of us
working together.

37:22.750 --> 37:26.330
As do I.

37:26.330 --> 37:28.170
Thank you,
President Rashad.

37:32.330 --> 37:34.960
[ Door opens, closes ]

37:34.960 --> 37:38.710
[ Breathes deeply ]

37:38.710 --> 37:40.920
[ Indistinct chatter ]

37:40.920 --> 37:43.420
I should've made more of
an effort to mingle or whatever.

37:43.420 --> 37:44.500
I'm sorry.

37:44.500 --> 37:45.920
Stop.

37:45.920 --> 37:47.960
You saved a head of state
instead.

37:47.960 --> 37:48.830
You did good, Huck.

37:48.830 --> 37:49.620
[ Sighs ]

37:49.620 --> 37:51.830
Abby.

37:57.540 --> 37:59.960
What was that earlier,
the hand holding?

37:59.960 --> 38:01.330
I was moved by the music.

38:01.330 --> 38:04.000
Yeah, well, let the music
move you and you alone.

38:04.000 --> 38:06.420
But why, when you're there,
right next to me?

38:06.420 --> 38:08.210
Because we're friends --

38:08.210 --> 38:11.330
Friends who do not
hold hands.

38:11.330 --> 38:13.500
We're good together, Abby.

38:13.500 --> 38:16.620
Look me in the eye
and tell me we aren't.

38:16.620 --> 38:18.880
[ Stevie Wonder's
"Joy Inside My Tears" plays ]

38:18.880 --> 38:20.500
[ Sighs ]

38:20.500 --> 38:22.420
I have to go.

38:24.620 --> 38:27.290
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

38:27.290 --> 38:28.960
Quinn: Oh, God.

38:28.960 --> 38:32.420
[ Exhales sharply,
groans ]

38:32.420 --> 38:34.330
You're awfully quiet.

38:34.330 --> 38:36.080
[ Sighs ]
You're never quiet.

38:36.080 --> 38:37.670
You told everyone
we were married.

38:37.670 --> 38:39.750
So...?
So, we're not.

38:39.750 --> 38:42.290
[ Sighs ] It's a really
conservative room, Charlie.

38:42.290 --> 38:44.040
It was easier to tell them
what they wanted to hear.

38:44.040 --> 38:45.250
Why's that such a problem?

38:45.250 --> 38:46.120
It's a problem
'cause we're not married

38:46.120 --> 38:47.380
and we should've been
by now.

38:47.380 --> 38:48.460
You said you were okay
with waiting

38:48.460 --> 38:49.880
until we got the firm
back up and running.

38:49.880 --> 38:52.670
I was.

38:52.670 --> 38:54.210
But...?

38:54.210 --> 38:56.750
♪ So I've tried to ♪

38:56.750 --> 38:59.710
But maybe it's too late.

38:59.710 --> 39:01.250
♪ Fall into that line ♪

39:01.250 --> 39:04.000
[ Scoffs ]

39:04.000 --> 39:06.080
What are you saying?

39:06.080 --> 39:09.500
I'm saying Quinn and Charlie
were a good match.

39:09.500 --> 39:12.620
But the New Quinn
of Quinn Perkins and Associates?

39:12.620 --> 39:13.620
She doesn't need
a Charlie.

39:13.620 --> 39:15.290
She needs a Kevin --

39:15.290 --> 39:17.500
Kevin who can go to dinner
and schmooze

39:17.500 --> 39:19.250
and [Inhales]
comes from a good family

39:19.250 --> 39:20.460
that plays polo
in Santa Barbara

39:20.460 --> 39:22.040
and fits into that world
without having to pretend

39:22.040 --> 39:23.210
that he belongs there?

39:23.210 --> 39:24.790
I-I can't.

39:24.790 --> 39:26.040
Not for long, anyway.

39:26.040 --> 39:27.620
The ruse won't hold,
and I think you know that.

39:27.620 --> 39:29.830
You just don't want
to say it.

39:34.710 --> 39:36.880
Screw you!

39:36.880 --> 39:38.500
You're dumping me?!
What?

39:38.500 --> 39:40.040
We're having a baby!

39:40.040 --> 39:42.710
I am not dumping you!
You're dumping me!

39:42.710 --> 39:44.540
Why the hell would you
even think that?!
You hit me!

39:44.540 --> 39:46.670
Because you're saying
stupid things!

39:46.670 --> 39:48.670
[ Breathing heavily ]

